# Synthetic Users Lab — Cursor Rules

## Design System
- Use Plinng DS tokens from `src/styles/tokens.ts` for ALL styling
- Never hardcode colors — always reference token constants
- Buttons are pill-shaped (border-radius: 9999px)
- Three button variants: Primary (black), Secondary (lime #BEFF50), Tertiary (white + border)
- Cards use `shadowSm` only, `borderRadius: rXl` (16px), border `#EBEBEB`
- Font: Inter at weights 400, 600, 700, 800
- Background: beige-25 (#FBFBF7), cards: white

## Architecture
- Components in `src/components/` — keep them small and focused
- Business logic in `src/lib/` — simulation, data, utils
- Types in `src/types/` — shared interfaces
- Tokens in `src/styles/tokens.ts` — mirror of CSS @theme tokens

## Patterns
- Modal follows plinng-ds Modal pattern: focus trap, backdrop blur, escape to close
- Badge uses dot indicator system with 5 variants (default, success, warning, error, info)
- Avatar component generates initials with persona-specific colors
- All status colors mapped to DS tokens (error-1, warning-1, accent-700, info-1)

## API
- Claude Sonnet 4 via Anthropic API
- max_tokens: 4096
- JSON response with repair/fallback logic in `src/lib/simulation.ts`
- Response schema: { score, summary, steps, issues, wouldReturn, verbatim }

## Conventions
- TypeScript strict mode
- Path aliases: `@/` → `src/`
- Functional components only
- Inline styles matching plinng-ds token system (migrating to Tailwind classes is a good next step)
